    {
      "id": "5949d26dbd1167015325b943092fd3e546acce02",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-06 10:26:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI'd remove SOM related bits (and subtest 132 from sanity) as the implementation will likely change and this won't happen very soon.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b594c966e3f344afdd94d1342d7afa63289aca7d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 7,
        "name": "Johann Lombardi",
        "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
        "username": "johann",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 15:38:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWell, the SOM test still seems to pass :)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f9ee805f3bcc81007afbc6f14af4909327d91c78",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 17:42:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (4 inline comments)\n\nOf course it will still pass if code writes and reads the same xattr. Real question is whether LMA handling will break if old (larger) LNA is too big to fit into current struct lustre_mdt_attrs?  Alternately, if new (smaller) LMAs are written, then MDS is downgraded, will this cause the old code to consider the LMA corrupted?\n\nI'm not so worried about SOM (which is just a cache) as just normal operations. If the smaller LMA causes problems on downgrade, then we'd need an incompat LMA flag, and backport a fix to allow 2.1.4 to accept the smaller LMA (though it at least needs to contain the FID).  Likewise, the new code should not be upset to see an LMA larger than the current struct size.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a5e572e4d45c4a18619f7bcf356ae091e1e83c35",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-07 18:32:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nMarking this -1 for now until the interop issues with LMA access are understood.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
