            "subject": "LU-1710 lvb: variable sized LVB support"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Johann Lombardi",
          "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-11-23 14:23:29.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
          "email": "aurelien.degremont@cea.fr",
          "date": "2012-12-13 17:20:39.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-2378 lma: move HSM & SOM attributes to dedicated xattrs",
        "message": "LU-2378 lma: move HSM & SOM attributes to dedicated xattrs\n\nReduce LMA to its minimum and move HSM & SOM attributes to dedicated\non-disk extented attributes. This is more consistent with the MDS\nlayering (HSM, LMA & SOM are managed in different layers) and avoids\nlocking + read/modify/write in many cases.\n\nAs far as interoperability is concerned, the old code works just fine\nif it reads a smaller LMA size and the new code retries with a\nlarger buffer on ERANGE error.\n\nSigned-off-by: Johann Lombardi <johann.lombardi@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Id4ee465ea69820229f7214d800821864330a8aec\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
